      "date": "2012-12-23 03:34:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThe insanity failure doesn't seem related to the patch. OST1 recovery hung in target_recovery_overseer() which did not wake up after a few recovery timeouts. I'm wondering why wait_event is used instead of instead of wait_event_timeout?\n\nI'll update the patch to address Andreas' comments.\n\n\nsome logs:\n09:45:51:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: recovery is timed out, evict stale exports\n09:45:51:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: disconnecting 1 stale clients\n09:46:22:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: recovery is timed out, evict stale exports\n09:46:22:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: Denying connection for new client lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov_UUID (at 10.10.4.142@tcp), waiting for all 4 known clients (2 recovered, 0 in progress, and 2 unseen) to recover in 0:29\n09:46:22:Lustre: Skipped 6 previous similar messages\n09:46:53:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: recovery is timed out, evict stale exports\n09:47:25:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: recovery is timed out, evict stale exports\n09:47:26:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: Denying connection for new client lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov_UUID (at 10.10.4.142@tcp), waiting for all 4 known clients (2 recovered, 0 in progress, and 2 unseen) to recover in 0:24\n09:47:26:Lustre: Skipped 12 previous similar messages\n09:47:57:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: recovery is timed out, evict stale exports\n09:49:39:Lustre: lustre-OST0000: Denying connection for new client lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov_UUID (at 10.10.4.142@tcp), waiting for all 4 known clients (2 recovered, 0 in progress, and 2 unseen) to recover in -1:-45\n09:49:39:Lustre: Skipped 25 previous similar messages\n09:51:42:INFO: task tgt_recov:27864 blocked for more than 120 seconds.\n09:51:42:\"echo 0 > /proc/sys/kernel/hung_task_timeout_secs\" disables this message.\n09:51:42:tgt_recov     D 0000000000000000     0 27864      2 0x00000080\n09:51:42: ffff88002dd8fe00 0000000000000046 ffff8800612dc558 000000000000001e\n09:51:42: 000000000000001e 0000000000000005 ffff88002dd8fdd0 ffffffffa0460591\n09:51:42: ffff880058